description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a part time (30 hours per week) Diabetes Specialist Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers and exciting opportunity for a Band 7 Diabetes Specialist Nurse in the Community Diabetes team for the East Cambs and Fenland area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post covers an interesting geographical area with a diverse population. Given the population that the service attends to we have developed an integrated model of care to better support rural community. The immediate team includes Diabetes Specialist Nurses and Diabetes Care Technicians and within the wider team there are also Diabetes Dietitians and Podiatrists. The post holder will also work closely with our partners in both primary and secondary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Benefits of working for CPFT include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave allowance 27 days plus bank holidays (this may increase depending on NHS service)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible job share opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff discount schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional development via the CPFT Academy which provides in-house training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stress awareness training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mindfulness training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Counselling service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occupational health support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sarah Beckett - Sarah.Beckett@cpft.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
